|x+1|+|y-2|=1 \Rightarrow |y-2|=1-|x+1|.
 |y-2|= \begin{cases} \,\,\,\,(y-2) \quad \operatorname{if} \,\,(y-2) \geq 0 \\ -(y-2) \quad\operatorname{if} \,\,(y-2) <0. \end{cases} 
 \begin{align*} (y-2)&=1-|x+1| \\ -(y-2)&=1-|x+1|. \end{align*} 
(y-2) \geq 0
1-|x+1|\geq 0 \Rightarrow |x+1|\leq 1 \Rightarrow -2 \leq x \leq 0.
(y-2)<0
-(y-2)>0
1-|x+1|>0  \Rightarrow |x+1|<1 \Rightarrow -2<x<0.
